headline.main: Rooms Wanted in the New City Hall.

docs.lead_paragraph: To night again the special order before the Councilmen is the report of the Committee on the New City Hall and the plan by them submitted. It is very natural that the Board should feel anxiety to bring the matter to a conclusion. The rooms are daily needed for use. It is creditable to them to be expeditious.

headline.main: LATEST INTELLIGENCE; By Telegraph to the New-York Daily Times Custom-House Appointments--Health of Caleb Cushing--The Treaty with the Netherlands.

docs.lead_paragraph: JOHN BROADHEAD of New-York, has been appointed a Special Inspector of the Customs at San Juan; and RAN RUNNELS of Texas, Inspector at Panama. CALEB CUSHING has recovered from his indisposition, and is now attending to the duties of his office.
docs.snippet: JOHN BROADHEAD of New-York, has been appointed a Special Inspector of the Customs at San Juan; and RAN RUNNELS of Texas, Inspector at Panama. CALEB CUSHING has recovered from his indisposition, and is now attending to the duties of his office.

docs.lead_paragraph: The report of Inspector DOWNING will be found in another column. As might have been anticipated the intense heat during a portion of last week resulted in an increase of the returns of deaths from cholera--though from cholera infantum there is a falling off from the report of last week. From cholera, 127 deaths are returned--it being an increase of 13 upon the number reported the previous week.

docs.lead_paragraph: Hon. E. H. FOSTER, of Nashville, whose death was briefly announced under the telegraphic head of yesterday, was, for more than twenty years, a prominent and popular politician in Tennessee. In 1820 he was Speaker of the lower branch of the State Legislature.

headline.main: Arrival of the Southern Mall--Melanchely Picture of Savannah--Yellow Fever, &c.

docs.lead_paragraph: New-Orleans papers of Saturday have been received. The Howard Association in New-Orleans had commenced taking care of the yellow fever patients. The Savannah Georgian gives a melaucholy picture of the health of Savannah.

docs.lead_paragraph: The Accessory Transit Company's steamship Star of the West, E. S. TINKLEPAUGH, Esq., Commander, from San Juan del Norte in 8 days and 6 hours, arrived at her wharf, Pier No. 3, N. R., at 6 o'clock yesterday morning.

headline.main: Dr. Cottman's Visit to the Czar--The Wrath of the London Times.

docs.lead_paragraph: Among the extracts from our English files received by the Africa, will be found a card from Sir HAMILTON SEYMOUR Contradicting some of the statements in Dr. COTTMAN's account of his interview with the Czar of Russia. We have already published the vehement vituperation of the London Times on this subject.
